    "At rst, automation almost exclusively benets labor, and the returns to capital are minuscule.",
    "But as automation increases and we come closer to Region 2, the wage bill reaches a ceiling and starts to decline.",
    "Further automation still raises output, but the returns to capital grow faster than output, at the expense of the wage bill.",
    "When Region 2 is reached at Φ = 0.5, both factors earn equal returns.",
    "Given equal endowments, this translates into capital and labor shares of one-half each."
  ],
